  "prompt": "Are there legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering at national and international levels:\n\n1. International Frameworks:\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n\n2. National Frameworks:\n- United States: Bank Secrecy Act\n- European Union: Anti-Money Laundering Directives\n- United Kingdom: Proceeds of Crime Act\n\n3. Key Prevention Mechanisms:\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n- Suspicious transaction reporting\n- Customer due diligence requirements\n- Mandatory financial institution compliance checks\n\n4. Typical Requirements:\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Record-keeping\n- Reporting large or suspicious transactions\n- Implementing internal control systems\n\n5. Enforcement Mechanisms:\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Significant financial penalties\n- Asset seizure\n- International cooperation between law enforcement agencies\n\nThese frameworks aim to detect, prevent, and prosecute money laundering activities across different jurisdictions and financial sectors.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any specific aspect of money laundering legal frameworks?",
